      "title": "Identifying Northern Mariana Islands",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/1_nmi_summary.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_location.png",
              "imageLink": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Northern_Mariana_Islands_in_Oceania_%28-mini_map_-rivers%29.svg/2388px-Northern_Mariana_Islands_in_Oceania_%28-mini_map_-rivers%29.svg.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The Northern Mariana Islands is a United States overseas territory. As such, it is counted as **the US** for country streaks purposes."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_car.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/e1TVSUpRgtRetpM26",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The entire Google car is blurred, however an antenna at the front right can be seen. The antenna is also **noticeably closer** to the camera than in the Guam Google car."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_pole.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/WcWY9Maj3jL19JjD9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Northern Mariana Islands have **wooden poles**, frequently with a crossbar at the top.",
              "NOTE: Guam typically has concrete poles."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "pole"
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/streetsign.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/3E6PHtcJLSiYhBBMA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The Northern Mariana Islands uses **blue** street signs, unlike Guam, which use green street signs."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_landscape.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/iqpm75XrCW6PDLw9A",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Northern Mariana Islands have a **tropical climate** with a lot of dense and somewhat low vegetation."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_redflower.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/tnw3drhwSREqtCtc6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Royal Poinciana, Flamboyant Tree or Flame Tree ([Delonix Regia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delonix_regia)) is the official tree of the Northern Mariana Islands and very common to see in the territory. Its **wide crown** with **bright red flowers** is easy to recognize.",
              "NOTE: This tree is not common in Guam."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_reflectorspam.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/UWyusyAu8qRihpKg9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Both Northern Mariana Islands and Guam often have a very **large number **of** road reflectors**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_asian.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/Mv91ffZwXQdu9UBe6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**East Asian languages** such as Japanese, Chinese, Korean, and even Russian are common to see in the Northern Mariana Islands.",
              "NOTE: This is also the case in Guam."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Regional clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_coveragemap.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_coveragemap.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The only island with car coverage is the main island of **Saipan**. The islands north of that have no coverage. Tinian and Sinapalu south of Saipan only have **tripod** coverage."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_towncentres.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/3ismHgYegwwX6C6a8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "**Dense commercial areas** can be found on the southern half of the west coast."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Spotlight",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/northern-mariana-islands/nmi_suicidecliff.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/abcbroprRxLYZe9y8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The **Suicide Cliff** is a steep cliff with a lot of exposed rock near the northern tip of the island."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
